Preliminaries and custom functions

Function to create unique species abbreviations.

spab <- function(tax=NULL,new.col=NULL ){
  nms <-  tax
  gen <- gsub("(\\w+) (\\w+)","\\1",nms)
  sp <- gsub("(\\w+) (\\w+)","\\2",nms)
  dt <- data.table(name=nms)
  for(i in 1:max(str_length(gen))){
    srch <- paste0("(\\w{",i,"}).+")
    gen2 <- gsub(srch,"\\1.",gen)
    dt[,paste0("ab",i):=gen2]
  }
  dt.m <- melt(dt,c("name"))
  dt.m[,min.n:=gsub("ab","",variable)]
  dt.m[,un:=!value %in% value[duplicated(value)]]
  dt.m <- dt.m[grepl("\\.",value)]
  ab <- dt.m[,.(ab=value[min(which(un=="TRUE"))]),by=.(name)][,sp.ab:=paste0(ab," ",sp)]
  return(ab)
}

#suprisingly, R doesn't have a built in std erro function
se <- function(x)(sd(x)/sqrt(length(x)))


rad <- function(x){
  if(abs(x)>180){x <- x-180}
  return(x*(pi/180))}

# extract Legend 
g_legend <- function(a.gplot){ 
  tmp <- ggplot_gtable(ggplot_build(a.gplot)) 
  leg <- which(sapply(tmp$grobs, function(x) x$name) == "guide-box") 
  legend <- tmp$grobs[[leg]] 
  return(legend)} 

legend <- g_legend(p)
